System Files: OS-specific metadata that clutters the repo.

Plaintext

.DS_Store          # macOS specific
Thumbs.db          # Windows specific
desktop.ini        # Windows specific
Logs & Temp Files: Files generated while the app is running.

Plaintext

*.log              # All log files
*.tmp              # Temporary files
*.swp              # Vim swap files
Secrets & Environment Variables: Critical for security.

Plaintext

.env               # Local environment variables
.env.local
*.pem              # Private keys/certificates
credentials.json   # API credentials
2. Language-Specific Files
Depending on your tech stack, you should ignore dependency folders and build artifacts.

JavaScript / Node.js
Plaintext

node_modules/       # Downloaded packages (too large to track)
dist/               # Build output
build/              # Build output
.npm/               # npm cache
Python
Plaintext

__pycache__/        # Compiled Python files
*.py[cod]           # Bytecode
venv/               # Virtual environment
.venv/
.pytest_cache/      # Testing cache
Java
Plaintext

*.class             # Compiled bytecode
*.jar               # Packaged archives
*.war
target/             # Maven build directory
build/              # Gradle build directory
C / C++
Plaintext

*.o                 # Object files
*.obj
*.exe               # Executables
*.out
*.so                # Shared libraries
